parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering hose clamp can cause power steering fluid leakage, leading to a loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, and potentially causing accidents or loss of control.

The failure of the power steering rack can cause power steering fluid leakage, leading to a loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, and potentially causing accidents or loss of control.

The failure of the power steering system can cause power steering fluid leakage, leading to a loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, and potentially causing accidents or loss of control.
The unintended activation of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause the vehicle to suddenly brake, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly brakes without warning
the brakes jam or lock up
the vehicle pulls to one side
the ABS light on the dashboard illuminates
the brake and accelerator pedals fail to function

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake malfunction can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake light on the dashboard illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Brake Assistance System (BAS) and Electronic Stability Program (ESP) can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The BAS/ESP light on the dashboard illuminates
the vehicle suddenly brakes or loses control
the brakes jam or lock up
the vehicle pulls to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, resulting in increased risk of injury or fatality. Additionally, sudden acceleration of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: airbag and supplemental restraining system warning lights remain illuminated
failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash
